# Service Registry

One row per long-running service this instance operates. Updated by `/init-service` and curated by humans.

| Service | Status | Port(s) | Container/Unit | Owner | Domain | CLAUDE.md | Notes |
|---------|--------|---------|----------------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|
| _example_ | active | 3000 | docker:example | derek | _instance | services/_example/CLAUDE.md | Example row, delete when first real service is added |

## Status values

- **active** — running normally
- **degraded** — running but unhealthy
- **stopped** — intentionally not running
- **unknown** — needs investigation
- **archived** — historical reference only

## Updating

Manually: edit this file. Programmatically: autonomous routines should propose changes via `system/proposals/` and `/promote`, never edit directly.
